Webshare offers proxies at a pretty fair price point. They even offer 10 with very limited bandwidth for free! For my use case I got pretty low requirements which they fulfill for just 3$/Month.The dashboard is nice and provides a great overview. The api provide full control over your proxies.The proxies generally work as expected. However I started experiencing early on minor annoyances. It started with multiple hour long api outages. One of my proxies where automatically replaced, however my app couldn’t update it, since the api was down. These outages happened on a regular basis (Once every 1-2 months)They also seemingly made a breaking api change, which required the request url path to end with / for some reason.Worst of all was the recent proxy issues. Proxies randomly stopped working, but wasn’t replaced as usual. The support answered once per day, but couldn’t provide me what I paid for, while this issue was ongoing. This cost me a lot of time, annoyed my users and decreased my revenue. It took 1 month to solve that issue. They are lucky that I was that patient, since any other customer would switch to another service. Reasons for staying with webshare remain the price, since competitors are at least 2x that expensive. And webshare provided me for  about half a year everything I needed mostly flawlessly.
